description.plain:
Clean Bandit is a UK electro pop-group, formed in Cambridge in 2008, consisting of Grace Chatto, and brothers Jack and Luke Patterson. They are known for their debut worldwide hit, “Rather Be”, and following songs like “Symphony”, “Rockabye” and “I Miss You”. They have worked with many talented artists, including Zara Larsson, Jess Glynne, Demi Lovato, Sean Paul, and Anne-Marie.

Many of their projects are known for blending elements of both classical and dance music, and featuring guest vocalists.

description.plain:
“Rockabye” is a dancehall song about all of the single and struggling mothers in the world. The track is the second single released from Clean Bandit’s second studio album What Is Love?, and their first single as a trio after violinist Neil Milan left the band earlier in the same week. It features guest vocals from Jamaican rapper Sean Paul and English singer Anne-Marie.

The song’s lyrics describe how single mothers bear hardships to raise their children and give them the best possible life, and the upbeat music turns that theme into a motivational track.

“Rockabye” was leaked onto the internet prematurely on the 20th October and was officially released the day after.

songs.title: Rather Be

description.plain:
The fourth single from Clean Bandit’s album New Eyes was written by the band along with songwriter Jimmy Napes and reportedly inspired by Rosie Gaines' “Closer Than Close”. The band enlisted Jess Glynne on the vocals after Grace Chatto heard her on “My Love” and thought “this voice is perfect for the song that we’ve written.”

“Rather Be” was a huge commercial success, debuting at number one on the UK charts and was the highest and fastest selling single of January 2014. In February 2014, the song shot past Daft Punk’s “Get Lucky” record with  1.09 million plays in a week on UK Spotify.

songs.full_title: Symphony by Clean Bandit (Ft. Zara Larsson)
songs.title: Symphony

description.plain:
“Symphony” is a song by British dance trio Clean Bandit. It is the third single from their sophomore album after the success of “Tears” and their global hit “Rockabye” which topped the UK charts. The song went on to top the UK Charts as well in April becoming Clean bandit’s third and Zara Larsson’s first #1 single in the UK.

“Symphony” features vocals from Zara Larsson with whom the band are touring with in 2017. This is the first collaboration between the artists.

They were filming the music video for the song in London on the last week of February.

https://twitter.com/cleanbandit/status/835768640909766657

The track is also featured as the final track on Zara Larsson’s debut international album “So Good”.

94 ContributorsTranslationsPortuguêsDeutschفارسیSymphony Lyrics[Verse 1]
I've been hearin' symphonies
Before, all I heard was silence
A rhapsody for you and me
And every melody is timeless
Life was stringin' me along
Then you came and you cut me loose
Was solo, singin' on my own
Now I can't find the key without you

[Pre-Chorus]
And now your song is on repeat
And I'm dancin' on to your heartbeat
And when you're gone, I feel incomplete
So, if you want the truth
[Chorus]
I just wanna be part of your symphony
Will you hold me tight and not let go?
Symphony
Like a love song on the radio
Will you hold me tight and not let go?

I'm sorry if it's all too much
